# =============================================================================
# harness/config.env — shared defaults for manual/interactive driver.py runs
# Brief: Rev6 (corrected)
#
# All values here are DEFAULTS only. Any value already exported in the
# environment before this file is sourced is left untouched (":${VAR:=...}"
# guards), so `STACK_ID=C7 N_TRIALS=1 bash harness/run_attacks.sh` overrides
# these correctly. The old version of this file assigned plainly (VAR=...),
# which silently clobbered anything the caller had already exported — that
# bug is fixed here.
#
# Driver/constants.py remains the single source of truth for condition
# membership, tenant namespaces, technique sets, and sample sizes. Nothing
# below should be treated as authoritative if it ever disagrees with
# Driver/constants.py — update constants.py first, this file second.
# =============================================================================

# Primary sequential build: C0..C7 (8 conditions). C0 = base layer (L2) only;
# C7 = full stack (L2,L1,L3a,L3b,L4,L5,L6,L7). There is no separate "ML
# detective layer" condition — that was leftover language from a pre-Rev6
# draft and did not correspond to anything in the 8-layer model.
: "${CONFIGS:=C0 C1 C2 C3 C4 C5 C6 C7}"

: "${ATTACKS:=attack1 attack2 attack3 attack4 attack5 attack6 attack7}"

# Brief default is N=50 trials per (config, attack) cell (Section 4).
# Override with a smaller N_TRIALS for a quick manual/smoke run, e.g.:
#   N_TRIALS=1 STACK_ID=C0 bash harness/run_attacks.sh
: "${N_TRIALS:=50}"
: "${BASE_SEED:=42}"
: "${DL_TIMEOUT:=300}"
: "${ATTACK_TIMEOUT:=90}"

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tenant namespaces (Driver/constants.TENANTS) — reference only.
#
# There is deliberately NO single ATTACKER / VICTIM / PARTNER1 / PARTNER2
# override here. The old config.env set one global attacker/victim pair for
# every attack class, which is wrong under the brief: each attack class has
# its own required attacker origin (Driver/constants.ATTACKER_NS_MAP), and
# A6/A7 additionally require origin == target (no namespace crossing).
# driver.py is what sets ATTACKER_NS / VICTIM_NS correctly, per class, per
# trial — this harness does not, and should not, try to do that itself.
#
#   tenant-lowpriv   restricted namespace; foothold for A1, A2, A5; default
#                    cross-tenant origin for classes without a more specific rule
#   tenant-finserv   isolated victim (mock PII); attack target for A1/A3/A7;
#                    origin == target for A6 and A7 (insider model, no
#                    namespace crossing)
#   tenant-partner   scoped, legitimate cross-namespace binding; origin for
#                    all A3 trials (see note on A4 below)
#   tenant-saas      higher-replica tenant; pivot hop for A5, burst-load
#                    source referenced in A7's context
#
# NOTE: A4's origin (tenant-lowpriv vs tenant-partner) is ambiguous in the
# brief itself — Driver/constants.py currently resolves it to tenant-partner
# with a comment flagging the ambiguity. Not resolved here; see prior
# validation notes before treating that as final.
#
# The legacy acme/globex/initech/umbrella naming is retired. Do not
# reintroduce it anywhere, including in ad-hoc overrides of this file.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Stratus / external wrapper integration: the pre-Rev6 harness referenced
# attacks/wrappers/ for this, but that directory does not exist in the
# current repo layout (Attacks/, Controls/, Driver/ only). Left disabled;
# re-enable and point DRIVER/WRAP at the right paths if that integration is
# reintroduced.
: "${USE_STRATUS:=0}"
